Today’s the first day of Kwanzaa, so Habari Gani! It’s also Boxing Day for the folks across the pond, but we out here starting with Umoja today.
Umoja is the first principle of Kwanzaa, and it simply means unity. It’s all about us striving to stay together and holding it down for the family, the community, and the culture as a whole.
Dr. Maulana Karenga created Kwanzaa back in 1966. He wanted us to have a way to celebrate our roots and keep our community tight, so he pulled it all together during the Black Freedom Movement.
Hell yeah it is! Dr. Karenga wasn't playing when he put that together for the culture—it's straight up for us and by us. It don't get much more authentic than that, for real.
